      <div class="blog-body">
        <h2>What Is the ECO4 Scheme?</h2>
        <p>ECO4 stands for Energy Company Obligation 4. It is a UK government programme that legally requires large energy suppliers to fund energy efficiency improvements in eligible homes. For qualifying Liverpool households, this can mean a free replacement boiler, first-time central heating installation, insulation and other heating upgrades at no cost to the homeowner or tenant.</p>
        <p>The scheme was launched in April 2022 and is administered by <a href="https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/faqs-domestic-consumers-and-landlords" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ofgem</a>. It runs until 31 December 2026. The government's successor programme, the Warm Homes Plan, is expected to follow. The ECO4 scheme focuses specifically on improving the least energy-efficient homes and helping households most vulnerable to fuel poverty.</p>

        <div class="blog-callout">
          <strong>ECO4 funding is limited and first-come, first-served</strong>
          <p>Energy companies have fixed budgets under ECO4 and allocate them on a first-come, first-served basis. Most remaining funding is now concentrated on the least efficient properties. If you think you may qualify, checking eligibility now rather than in six months is strongly advisable.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Who Qualifies for ECO4 in Liverpool?</h2>
        <p>To qualify for ECO4, a Liverpool household must meet two main criteria: income or benefit eligibility and property energy efficiency rating.</p>

        <h3>Income and benefit eligibility</h3>
        <p>You must be receiving at least one of the following qualifying benefits:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Universal Credit</li>
          <li>Pension Credit (Guarantee or Savings Credit)</li>
          <li>Housing Benefit</li>
          <li>Income-based Jobseeker's Allowance (JSA)</li>
          <li>Income-related Employment and Support Allowance (ESA)</li>
          <li>Income Support</li>
          <li>Child Tax Credit</li>
          <li>Working Tax Credit</li>
          <li>Child Benefit (subject to an income threshold)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Property energy efficiency</h3>
        <p>Your Liverpool property must have an EPC (Energy Performance Certificate) rating of D, E, F or G. Properties already rated A, B or C are not eligible because they are considered sufficiently energy-efficient. The EPC rating can be checked for free on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/check-energy-performance-certificate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GOV.UK EPC checker</a>. If your property has not had an EPC assessment, one can be arranged as part of the ECO4 eligibility process.</p>

        <h3>ECO4 Flex: if you do not receive qualifying benefits</h3>
        <p>If your household does not receive a qualifying benefit but has a low income or specific health vulnerabilities that are worsened by living in a cold home, you may still qualify through the ECO4 Flex route. Under Flex, your local council can refer your household for ECO4 funding if you meet their local eligibility criteria. Each Liverpool City Council ward may have different Flex criteria. Contact <a href="https://liverpool.gov.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Liverpool City Council</a> to ask whether your household might qualify under Flex.</p>

        <h2>What Can ECO4 Fund in Liverpool?</h2>
        <p>ECO4 takes a whole-house approach to energy efficiency. Rather than replacing a boiler in isolation, the scheme assesses the whole property and funds the combination of measures that delivers the greatest energy efficiency improvement. For Liverpool properties, this typically includes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Replacement of an old inefficient boiler with a new A-rated condensing boiler</li>
          <li>First-time central heating installation in properties with no existing system</li>
          <li>Loft insulation where not already present to current standards</li>
          <li>Cavity wall insulation in properties with unfilled cavities</li>
          <li>Solid wall insulation (internal or external) for Victorian properties without cavity walls</li>
          <li>Smart heating controls as part of a broader upgrade</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Not every measure is available to every property. An assessor will survey your Liverpool home and determine which combination of measures delivers the required improvement in energy efficiency rating.</p>

        <h2>What ECO4 Does Not Cover</h2>
        <p>ECO4 is specifically for replacing inefficient gas heating systems or installing central heating for the first time. It does not fund:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Boiler repairs or servicing (it funds replacement, not maintenance)</li>
          <li>Electric boiler installations in gas-connected properties</li>
          <li>Heat pumps (these are funded separately under the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-boiler-upgrade-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Upgrade Scheme</a>)</li>
          <li>Properties already rated C or above on their EPC</li>
          <li>Social housing (there are separate schemes for this sector)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Apply for ECO4 in Liverpool</h2>
        <p>There is no direct government application form for ECO4. The scheme is delivered by approved installers who work with energy company budgets. The process is:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Check your EPC rating at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/check-energy-performance-certificate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gov.uk/check-energy-performance-certificate</a></li>
          <li>Confirm you receive a qualifying benefit or check Flex eligibility with Liverpool City Council</li>
          <li>Contact us on 0151 558 0334. we assess ECO4 eligibility at our free survey at no cost to you</li>
          <li>If eligible, an approved energy assessor visits your property to confirm qualifying measures</li>
          <li>Approved measures are installed by certified engineers at no cost to you</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>What Happens After ECO4? The Warm Homes Plan</h2>
        <p>The UK government has announced the Warm Homes Plan as the successor to ECO4, with £13.2 billion in funding allocated. The Warm Homes: Local Grant programme is already underway in some areas, focusing on improving the least energy-efficient homes with insulation, low-carbon heating systems and smart controls. Liverpool households who miss the ECO4 window should register their interest for Warm Homes Plan funding as these programmes are announced. See the latest government guidance on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-great-british-insulation-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GOV.UK</a> for updates.</p>

        <div class="blog-success">
          <strong>We assess ECO4 eligibility at the free survey at no cost</strong>
          <p>If you think you may qualify, call us on 0151 558 0334. We assess eligibility during the free survey and advise on the best route forward. If ECO4 is not available, we can also advise on low-cost finance options for boiler replacement. <a href="/boiler-installation-liverpool" style="color:#15803d;">See our boiler installation page</a> for standard installation prices.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="pf-faq">
          <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">ELIGIBLE</span>&nbsp; How do I know if I qualify for ECO4 in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>You need to receive a qualifying benefit (Universal Credit, Pension Credit, Housing Benefit and others) and have an EPC rating of D, E, F or G. Check your EPC rating free at gov.uk/check-energy-performance-certificate. We assess full eligibility during the free survey at no cost. Call 0151 558 0334.</p></div></details>
          <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">FREE</span>&nbsp; Is a new boiler completely free under ECO4?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>For qualifying households, yes. The full cost of the boiler, installation, controls and any required insulation measures is covered by the energy company at no cost to you. In some complex installations a small contribution may be required. This will be confirmed before any work is agreed.</p></div></details>
          <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">TENANT</span>&nbsp; Can tenants apply for ECO4 funding in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Private tenants can receive ECO4 funding if they receive qualifying benefits and the property has a qualifying EPC rating. The landlord must give written consent for the work. The landlord does not need to receive benefits. It is the tenant's benefit status that determines eligibility.</p></div></details>
          <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">DEADLINE</span>&nbsp; When does ECO4 end?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>The ECO4 scheme runs until 31 December 2026. Remaining funding is limited and allocated first-come, first-served. The government's Warm Homes Plan is the expected successor programme. If you think you may qualify, checking eligibility now is strongly advisable.</p></div></details>
          <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">FLEX</span>&nbsp; What is ECO4 Flex and do I need qualifying benefits?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>ECO4 Flex allows local councils to refer households for ECO4 funding even if they do not receive a qualifying benefit, if they meet local vulnerability or low income criteria. Liverpool City Council sets its own Flex criteria. Contact Liverpool City Council to check whether your household might qualify through the Flex route.</p></div></details>
        </div>
      </div>

